From Franklin Antonio Subject Re Thermoscan ear thermometer In article Ashwin Ram writes Does the Thermoscan instrument really work It is supposed to give you a fast and accurate temperature reading in the How far in the ear does one have to insert the instrument Is it worth the it is currently selling for No they do not work My doctor started using one recently and I thought the concept was so amazing that I bought one The thing works by reading the infrared emissions from the ear The ear drum is hotter than the ear canal walls so you have to point the thing very This means tugging on the top of the ear to straighten out the ear canal then inserting the thing snugly then pushing a Unfortunately there are many things that can go It is almost impossible to aim the thing correctly when you do it on I get readings which differ from each other by up to degrees and may differ from an oral thermometer by up to I talked to one of the nurses in my doctor's office recently about this and she said she didn't like them either for same She did give me some instruction on how to tug on my ear and what correct insertion feels like but she said she thought it was impossible to do correctly on one's She also said that she and other nurses had complained to the company about inaccurate readings and that someone from the company had told them to take great care to clean the infrared window at the end of the probe with alcohol from time to She demonstrated this prior to reading my temperature and managed to get a reading within degree of the oral temperature I took at home before driving to the Dr's I have also noticed tha some nurses click the button then remove the probe This causes wrong In my experience you have to leave the probe in a good to seconds after clicking the button to get a good The nurse I talked with I suspect that many people don't realize this and therefore get bad readings for yet another In short it's a great It may work for some folks but I believe it doesn't wo